-- Peugeot Citroen Isn't Facing Fuel Supply Difficulties, La Tribune Reports
-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 2010-10-21T04:31:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/peugeot-citroen-isn-t-facing-fuel-supply-difficulties-la-tribune-reports.html
PSA Peugeot Citroen is not facing
fuel-supply difficulties as a result of French strikes and its
factories are working normally, La Tribune reported, citing
Chief Financial Officer Frederic Saint-Geours, who spoke in an
interview with BFM radio station.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Whitehouse at 
